I really like this, and you've got a +1, but one note: You refer to this as an orbital station, but never say what it's orbiting. At a distance of 16 light years, it's probably not our sun: at those ranges an elliptical orbit would be better described as . Highly eccentric orbits would be implausible at that distance, too. At perigee you'd either be screaming past the sun at speeds best measured in percentages of the speed of light or way beyond the heliosphere.







